It was great. Only four cause certain points at the movies should have been left alone.

A great movie, encumbered by having to fix a fairly enormous list of things Rian Johnson got so terribly wrong in the Last Jedi, but Abrams makes a good fist of it.

Great things the movie does: 

General Hux (3 stooges comedy version) - dead.

Rose - told to go and read a book instead of being in the movie.

Luke - catches his lightsaber and pointedly says that nobody should ever throw one away (Rian, he's talking to you...)

Chewie doesn't actually die off screen for no reason without fanfare - unlike trilogy hero Admiral Ackbar.

Undoes Rian Johnson's "Kill the past" idea in the very first words - "The dead speak!"

Gets the heroes of the movie to hang out together.

Fixes Luke's lightsaber which Rian broke.

Fixes Kylos helmet which Rian broke.

Fixes Rey's parents backstory which Rian broke.

Fixes Luke X Wing, which Rian broke.

Re-films Reys dark side vision (the one with evil Rey), which Rian got wrong (the drawn out meaningless one with mirror Reys).

Points out that Holdo flying a ship at lightspeed at anything kills it, was just a dumb idea.

Discusses gravity, instead of ignoring it.

Explains Snoke.

Makes Rey practice hard to be good.

Makes the movie fun and enjoyable (unlike the Last Jedi).

Not a perfect movie, and hampered by the idiot they put in charge of the last movie, but overall pretty close to greatness.

Makes you wonder how brilliant this trilogy would have been with the consistency of one director throughout, instead of dumping a blithering clown in to run the second movie.
